cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is related to natural language processing and information retrieval, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it covers research related to natural language processing. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of statistical evidence from Google search engine. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories as they cover probabilistic approaches and statistical modeling. Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but it is possible as the paper discusses the linguistic evidence gathered from parsed text.
